## Pulling the reconciled stack down to a local clone

CI is the writer; a local clone only goes stale. Because `sync-upstream`
force-rebases `distro/nix` and `main`, a plain `git pull` will report divergence.
Use the local synchronizer instead, which resets/rebases each rail to the
GitHub tip without losing local-only work and auto-stashes a dirty tree:

```sh
scripts/sync-local.sh --check   # report drift, change nothing
scripts/sync-local.sh           # reconcile vendor/upstream, distro/nix, main
```

Policy per rail:

- `vendor/upstream`: hard-reset to `github/vendor/upstream` (mirror; aborts loud
  if it somehow carries local-only commits).
- `distro/nix`, `main`: reset when the local branch is strictly behind, otherwise
  rebase local commits onto the GitHub tip. A rebase conflict aborts cleanly and
  leaves the branch untouched.

After syncing `main`, bump the consumer pin (see below).

## End-to-end maintenance loop

```mermaid
flowchart LR
  U["upstream/master<br/>1jehuang/jcode"] -->|"6h scheduler<br/>(fork-maintenance.yml)"| CI
  CI["nix.yml sync-upstream:<br/>ff vendor/upstream,<br/>rebase distro/nix, then main<br/>(force-with-lease)"] --> GH["github/jerudnik:<br/>vendor/upstream<br/>distro/nix<br/>main"]
  GH -->|"nix.yml build matrix"| CX["Cachix:<br/>jerudnik-jcode.cachix.org<br/>(prebuilt x86_64/aarch64-linux,<br/>aarch64-darwin)"]
  GH -->|"scripts/sync-local.sh"| L["local clone<br/>~/infrastructure/jcode"]
  GH -->|"nix flake update jcode"| FX["4nix consumer<br/>jcode.url = github:jerudnik/jcode/main"]
  CX -.->|"substituter<br/>(no local rebuild)"| FX
  CX -.->|"substituter"| L
```

Surfaces and their owners:

| Surface | Updated by | Authoritative? |
|---|---|---|
| `upstream/master` | upstream maintainers | source of truth for upstream code |
| `github/{vendor,distro/nix,main}` | `Fork maintenance` CI every 6h | yes (only writer) |
| Cachix `jerudnik-jcode` | `nix.yml` build matrix on push | prebuilt artifact cache |
| local clone | `scripts/sync-local.sh` | read-only mirror of GitHub |
| 4nix `jcode` input | `nix flake update jcode` in `~/infrastructure/4nix` | consumer pin |

The Cachix cache is what keeps real-time local resource use low: 4nix and local
`nix build` pull prebuilt binaries from `jerudnik-jcode.cachix.org` (trusted in
`4nix/modules/defaults.nix`) instead of recompiling the Rust workspace.

## Updating the 4nix consumer pin

4nix consumes `jcode.url = "github:jerudnik/jcode/main"`. Its `flake.lock` pins a
specific `main` rev and only moves when you bump it:

```sh
cd ~/infrastructure/4nix
nix flake update jcode          # repin jcode/main to the latest reconciled tip
nix flake check                 # or the repo's preflight/validation gate
git commit -m "chore(flake): bump jcode" flake.lock
```

Prefer bumping after the GitHub `Nix` build matrix is green for that `main` rev,
so the Cachix cache is already populated and the consumer never builds jcode
locally.

